  <h2 style="text-align:center;">Update on Graduation and other Spring Activities</h2>
  <p>All Schools in Wayne County are closed for the remainder of the year per Governors Orders.  Graduation for Tolsia High School is scheduled for May 27, 2020.  Graduation for Spring Valley High School and Wayne High School are scheduled for Saturday, May 23, 2020.  If the closure of schools in the State of West Virginia continues or if Social Distancing guidelines are extended through the month of May, Graduation Ceremonies at all three high schools will be postponed.  The Board of Education and Staff at Spring Valley High School, Tolsia High School, and Wayne High School are committed to ensuring that all graduating seniors participate in a graduation ceremony.  If graduation is delayed, we will reschedule for June 25, 2020 (Tolsia High School) and June 27, 2020 (Spring Valley High School and Wayne High School).  Later dates will be considered if the COVID-19 virus prevents the ceremony from occurring in June.</p>
  <p>Other Spring Activities including Prom cannot take place during a school closure or while Social Distancing Guidelines are in effect.  It is unlikely that any spring events will occur due to the possibility that social distancing guidelines will continue through the summer.  It is necessary to cancel the Prom events for all three high schools originally scheduled in early to mid-May due to COVID-19 health concerns.
Please monitor the Districts website at wayneschoolswv.org for the latest information regarding school closure.
</p>
